Enum Call.VideoRenderMode

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<Call.VideoRenderMode>

    public static enum Call.VideoRenderMode
extends java.lang.Enum<Call.VideoRenderMode>
    The options to specify how the video adjusts its content to be render in a view.
    Since:
    2.6.0

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      CropFill
      The option to scale the video to fill the size of the view.
      Fit
      The option to scale the video to fit the size of the view by maintaining the aspect ratio.
      StretchFill
      The option to scale the video to fit the size of the view by changing the aspect ratio of the video if necessary.

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • Fit

        public static final Call.VideoRenderMode Fit
        The option to scale the video to fit the size of the view by maintaining the aspect ratio. The black paddings will be added to the remaining area of the view.

      • CropFill

        public static final Call.VideoRenderMode CropFill
        The option to scale the video to fill the size of the view. Some portion of the video may be cropped.

      • StretchFill

        public static final Call.VideoRenderMode StretchFill
        The option to scale the video to fit the size of the view by changing the aspect ratio of the video if necessary.
